    "*Exercise 4:* Write a function that takes an `n×n` matrix representing a tic‑tac‑toe game and returns one of the following values:\n",
    "\n",
    "- `-1` if the game is **incomplete** (still empty spaces and no winner)\n",
    "- `0` if the game is a **draw**\n",
    "- `1` if **player 1** (`\"X\"`) has won\n",
    "- `2` if **player 2** (`\"O\"`) has won\n",
    "\n",
    "Here are some example inputs you can use to test your code:\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 48,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def check_winner(board):\n",
    "    n = len(board)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # check rows\n",
    "    for r in range(n):\n",
    "        if board[r][0] != 0:\n",
    "            same = True\n",
    "            for c in range(n):\n",
    "                if board[r][c] != board[r][0]:\n",
    "                    same = False\n",
    "                    break\n",
    "            if same:\n",
    "                return board[r][0]\n",
    "\n",
    "    # check columns\n",
    "    for c in range(n):\n",
    "        if board[0][c] != 0:\n",
    "            same = True\n",
    "            for r in range(n):\n",
    "                if board[r][c] != board[0][c]:\n",
    "                    same = False\n",
    "                    break\n",
    "            if same:\n",
    "                return board[0][c]\n",
    "\n",
    "    # main diagonal\n",
    "    if board[0][0] != 0:\n",
    "        same = True\n",
    "        for i in range(n):\n",
    "            if board[i][i] != board[0][0]:\n",
    "                same = False\n",
    "                break\n",
    "        if same:\n",
    "            return board[0][0]\n",
    "\n",
    "    # other diagonal\n",
    "    if board[0][n-1] != 0:\n",
    "        same = True\n",
    "        for i in range(n):\n",
    "            if board[i][n-1-i] != board[0][n-1]:\n",
    "                same = False\n",
    "                break\n",
    "        if same:\n",
    "            return board[0][n-1]\n",
    "\n",
    "    # check for empty spaces\n",
    "    for r in range(n):\n",
    "        for c in range(n):\n",
    "            if board[r][c] == 0:\n",
    "                return -1\n",
    "\n",
    "    return 0\n"
